He revealed 500 of Vladimir Putin's soldiers are treating the plant "like a shield". The Ministry of Defence warned Moscow is reinforcing defences in southern Ukraine.  Kyiv has vowed to retake regions - but Mr Kotin insisted the Putin plan is to disconnect the plant from Ukraine's grid and connect it to Russia's network. Pavlo Kyrylenko, head of the Donetsk region, said: "The shelling is constant and the enemy is also using air strikes - but it is having no success. Donetsk is holding." 